<module>
    <h>latha</h>
    <p><g>latha</g>
        <masc/>
        <en>a day</en></p>

    <section>
        <h>adjectives</h>
        <module id="math">
            <h>math</h>
            <p><g>latha <a href="?gd=math">math</a></g>
                <en>a good day</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha latha math ann an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>It’s a good day today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 12</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Ma bhitheas latha math ann am màireach, thèid sinn do’n mhonadh.</gd>
                        <tr>If it is a good day tomorrow, we shall go to the moor.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 50</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </module>
        <module id="briagha">
            <h>briagha</h>
            <p><g>latha <a href="?gd=briagha">briagha</a></g>
                <en>a beautiful day</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha latha briagha blàth ann.</gd>
                        <tr>It is a beautiful warm day.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [228]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha latha briagha ann agus bha a’ ghrian a’ deàrrsadh.</gd>
                        <tr>It was a beautiful day and the sun was shining.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td 21</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha Calum sgìth a’ coiseachd air a’ mhonadh, ach mu dheireadh ràinig e
                            mullach na beinne. [...] Bha latha briagha ann agus bha a’ ghrian a’
                            deàrrsadh. Cha robh neul anns an adhar.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm was tired walking on the moor, but at last he reached the top of
                            the mountain. [...] It was a beautiful day and the sun was shining.
                            There wasn’t a cloud in the sky.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 146</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </module>
        <module id="blaath">
            <h>blàth</h>
            <p><g>latha <a href="?gd=blaath">blàth</a></g>
                <en>a warm day</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha latha briagha blàth ann.</gd>
                        <tr>It is a beautiful warm day.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [228]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Dh’ fhàg Màiri agus Seumas an taigh tràth anns a’ mhadainn. Bha an latha
                            blàth, agus bha na h-eòin a’ seinn anns na craobhan.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary and James left the house early in the morning. The day was warm,
                            and the birds were singing in the trees.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 76 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </module>
        <module id="fuar">
            <h>fuar</h>
            <p><g>latha <a href="?gd=fuar">fuar</a></g>
                <en>a cold day</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an latha fuar?</gd>
                        <tr>Is the day cold?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha an latha fuar agus cha do dh’fhàg sinn an taigh.</gd>
                        <tr>The day was cold and we did not leave the house.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 238</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </module>
    </section>

