        <module id="fad">
            <h>fad</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=fad">fad</a> [an] latha</g>
                <en>length of the day, all day long</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An robh an gille seo anns an sgoil an diugh? Cha robh, bha e anns an
                            taigh fad an latha.</gd>
                        <tr>Was this boy in the school today? No, he was in the house all day
                            long.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An robh an clachair ag obair air a’ bhalla fad an latha an dé? Bha.</gd>
                        <tr>Was the mason working on the wall all day yesterday? Yes, he was.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
        <!-- </section>-->
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>verbs</h>
        <section>
            <h>subject</h>
            <module id="coord">
                <h>còrd</h>
                <p><g><a href="?gd=coord">còrd</a> latha ri ...</g>
                    <en>... enjoys a day, a day agrees with ...</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Bha Calum sgìth a’ coiseachd air a’ mhonadh, ach mu dheireadh ràinig
                                e mullach na beinne. Bha càrn chlach air mullach na beinne. Chuir
                                Calum clach air a’ chàrn agus shuidh e ri taobh a’ chùirn a’ leigeil
                                analach. [...] An ceann greise dh’éirich Calum ’na sheasamh agus
                                thearnaich e a’ bheinn air a shocair. Chòrd an latha gu math ris ach
                                bha an t-acras mór air nuair a ràinig e an taigh.</gd>
                            <tr>Malcolm was tired walking on the moor, but at last he reached the
                                top of the mountain. There was a cairn of stones on the top of the
                                mountain. Calum put a stone onto the cairn and he sat down beside
                                the cairn having a rest. [...] After a while Malcolm rose up and he
                                descended the mountain leisurely. He enjoyed the day well but he was
                                very hungry when he reached the house.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 146</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl>
                </p>
            </module>
        </section>
    </section>


